
{
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Converts casual work descriptions into properly formatted JIRA tickets. Routes to specialist formatters for Bugs, Stories, or Tasks based on intent.",
        "sample_queries": [
            "spent 3 hours debugging the login timeout issue on prod, turns out the redis session TTL was set to 5 seconds instead of 5 minutes",
            "need to add pagination to the users API endpoint, right now it returns all 50k records at once and the frontend crashes",
            "fixed the broken CI pipeline - the docker image tag was hardcoded to latest instead of using the git sha"
        ]
    },

    include "backend/registries/llm_config.hocon"

    "tools": [
        {
            "name": "TicketWriter",
            "function": {
                "description": "I turn casual work descriptions into properly formatted JIRA tickets. Just tell me what you did, what needs doing, or what broke - in your own words."
            },
            "instructions": """You are a JIRA ticket routing expert. Your job is to take the user's casual description and route it to the correct specialist formatter.

HOW TO ACT:
- Do NOT write preamble. Do NOT say "let me help you" or "I will create".
- Determine the ticket type from context and IMMEDIATELY call the appropriate specialist tool.
- After receiving the formatted ticket from the specialist, present it to the user exactly as returned.
- If the user asks to save or download the ticket, call SaveTicket with the formatted content.

ROUTING RULES:
- User describes something BROKEN, a defect, an error, or a fix they applied -> call BugTicketWriter
- User describes a NEW FEATURE, enhancement, or something that needs to be BUILT -> call StoryTicketWriter
- User describes WORK DONE, a task completed, maintenance, or routine work -> call TaskTicketWriter
- If ambiguous, default to TaskTicketWriter.

AFTER receiving the specialist's response, present it cleanly to the user. Do not modify the formatting.
""",
            "tools": ["BugTicketWriter", "StoryTicketWriter", "TaskTicketWriter", "SaveTicket"]
        },

        {
            "name": "BugTicketWriter",
            "function": {
                "description": "Formats a bug/defect JIRA ticket from a casual description.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "description": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The casual bug/defect description from the user."
                        }
                    },
                    "required": ["description"]
                }
            },
            "instructions": """You format bug/defect JIRA tickets. Given a casual description, produce this EXACT structure:

**Title**: [Concise bug title - describe the symptom, max 60 chars]

**Type**: Bug
**Priority**: [Critical/High/Medium/Low - infer from impact]
**Status**: [Open if unfixed, Done if user says they fixed it]

**Description**:
- **Symptom**: What went wrong
- **Root Cause**: Why it happened (if known)
- **Impact**: Who/what was affected
- **Fix Applied**: What was done (if already fixed)

**Steps to Reproduce** (if inferrable):
1. ...

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- [ ] The defect no longer occurs under the described conditions
- [ ] [Additional criteria based on context]

**Labels**: [2-3 relevant labels e.g. backend, production, auth, database]
**Time Spent**: [if mentioned by user]

Be concise and professional. Infer what you can, mark unknowns as TBD."""
        },

        {
            "name": "StoryTicketWriter",
            "function": {
                "description": "Formats a user story / feature request JIRA ticket from a casual description.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "description": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The casual feature/story description from the user."
                        }
                    },
                    "required": ["description"]
                }
            },
            "instructions": """You format user story / feature JIRA tickets. Given a casual description, produce this EXACT structure:

**Title**: [Action-oriented title starting with a verb, max 60 chars]

**Type**: Story
**Priority**: [High/Medium/Low - infer from urgency described]
**Status**: Open

**Description**:
- **As a** [user/developer/admin - infer from context]
- **I want** [what needs to be built]
- **So that** [business value / why it matters]

**Technical Approach** (if inferrable):
- Brief bullet points on how to implement

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- [ ] [Testable condition 1]
- [ ] [Testable condition 2]
- [ ] [Testable condition 3]

**Labels**: [2-3 relevant labels e.g. frontend, API, performance, UX]
**Estimate**: [Story points or hours - infer from complexity]

Be concise and professional. Infer what you can from context."""
        },

        {
            "name": "TaskTicketWriter",
            "function": {
                "description": "Formats a task / work-log JIRA ticket from a casual description.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "description": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The casual task/work description from the user."
                        }
                    },
                    "required": ["description"]
                }
            },
            "instructions": """You format task / work-log JIRA tickets. Given a casual description, produce this EXACT structure:

**Title**: [Concise task title starting with a verb, max 60 chars]

**Type**: Task
**Priority**: [Medium/Low - tasks are usually routine unless stated otherwise]
**Status**: [Done if user describes completed work, Open if it still needs doing]

**Description**:
- **What**: What was done or needs to be done
- **Why**: Context or reason (infer if not stated)
- **Outcome**: What changed or will change as a result

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- [ ] [Completion condition 1]
- [ ] [Completion condition 2]

**Labels**: [2-3 relevant labels e.g. devops, maintenance, infrastructure, documentation]
**Time Spent/Estimate**: [if mentioned]

**Notes**: [Any follow-up actions, dependencies, or related work]

Be concise and professional. Infer what you can from context."""
        },

        {
            "name": "SaveTicket",
            "function": {
                "description": "Saves the formatted JIRA ticket content so the user can download it. Always return the content back after saving.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "content": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The full formatted JIRA ticket content in Markdown."
                        },
                        "filename": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Optional filename (without extension)."
                        }
                    },
                    "required": ["content"]
                }
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.jira_ticket.save_ticket.SaveTicket"
        }
    ]
}
